  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

  <p>The MySQL sink allows you to write generated data directly to MySQL databases.</p>

  <h2 id="configuration">Configuration</h2>

  <p>Configure MySQL connection in <code>~/.datagenc/config.yaml</code>:</p>

  <pre><code>sinks:
  mysql:
    host: localhost
    port: 3306
    database: testdb
    username: root
    password: secret</code></pre>

  <Callout type="caution">
    <p>Never commit database credentials to version control. Use environment variables instead.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

  <p>Generate and insert data into MySQL:</p>

  <pre><code>datagenc gen users.dg --sink mysql --count 10000</code></pre>

  <p>The sink automatically:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Creates the table if it doesn't exist</li>
    <li>Batches inserts for performance</li>
    <li>Reports progress and errors</li>
  </ol>

